    <subfield code="o">36</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">Here we have solved the equation of motion of the shell [see Eq. (35) of [14]]: gin(r) + ˙R2 - gout(r) + ˙R2 = -m/r with ˙R = 0. Here gin(r) = 1 - 2M/r + Q2 /r2 and gout(r) = 1 - 2(M + E)/r + (Q + q)2 /r2</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">37</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">That is, rNH > r+ [see Eqs. (2) and (7)]</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">38</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">For example, a shell which starts falling from rest towards the black hole from spatial infinity would form a new horizon when reaching rNH = M +m+[(M +m)2 -(Q+ q)2]1/2</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="999" ind1="C" ind2="5">
    <subfield code="o">39</subfield>
    <subfield code="m">Our version of the gedanken experiment would be more challenging (from the point of view of the WCCC) than the one considered in [13]</subfield>
